name: Madewell Forest Floor Dress (10042011_1)
description:
This dress is screaming for a pair of boots. Woodsy chic gone psychedelic—we love the swirling woodgrain print as much as the flouncy, throw-it-on shape.

Loose fit.
Straight skirt.
Falls 35 5/8" from shoulder.
Silk georgette.
Dry clean.
Import.

Originally $168.00

name: J.Crew Silk Tricotine Sophia Dress (12082010_1)
description:
Yeah, yeah....they're supposed to be looking at the bride. But this dress is simply sexy - literally - on a bridesmaid or at a cocktail party. 

Pure midweight silk tricotine with a refined finish and an elegant drape. Shirring at bust. Overlap detail at front and back, with shoulder pleats. Lingerie straps to secure bra. Sleeveless. Side zip. A-line skirt. Fully lined. Falls below knee. Import. Dry clean. 

Originally $165.00.

name: DKNY Dress Pants ( 11132010_3)
description:
Elegance in a pant. Dress up, dress down – this designer cut will flatter your figure with the comfort of your fat pants (we all have some). Heels, boots or flats would make great teammates. Tenny-runners, not so much.

Made in Italy. (And you'll most likely have to get these hemmed to fit your inseam.)

47% Polyester
47% Viscose
7% Spandex.

Originally $195.00

name: J. Crew Bootcut Jean (09172010_5)
description:
Your buns will look good in these. Cotton with a hint of stretch. Belt loops. Zip fly. Traditional 5-pocket styling. Import. Machine wash.

Originally: $98.00

name: Anthropologie Embroidered Blouse (10262010_2)
description:
Pretty as a petal, this shirt is all lady. Beautiful embroidered flowers around the hem line. Tuxedo breast. With a velvet jacket over this, you're ready for the holidays. Or, if you holiday somewhere sunny -- skip the jacket and you're still looking good. Or heck, forget the holidays and wear this baby anywhere!

Originally $98.00
